<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Public Security Minister Meets With HK Police Commissioner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Tao Siju, minister of Public
Security, met this afternoon with Hui Ki-on, the Commissioner of
Police of Hong Kong, who is in Beijing for the 25th meeting
between INTERPOL organizations in Hong Kong and in the Chinese
inland area.
</P>
<P>
Tao welcomed Hui, who is a leading member of Hong Kong's
INTERPOL bureau, by congratulating him on being appointed
Commissioner of Police of the first government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
In the past 10 years or more, he said, positive results have
been achieved from cooperation between the police in the inland
area and Hong Kong in cracking down on criminal activities through
INTERPOL.
</P>
<P>
Tao said that, according to the provisions of the Basic Law of
the Hong Kong SAR, the security organizations in the inland areas
and the Hong Kong police department, which are not affiliated with
each other, will maintain links and support each other after Hong
Kong returns to the motherland, and their cooperation will become
more extensive, close, and effective.
</P>
<P>
Tao said he is completely confident that the Hong Kong police
will safeguard the stability of the final transition period and do
a good job in public security for the activities during the
return, and expressed the belief that the mainland and Hong Kong
police departments will cooperate in a better way.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting, Zhu Entao, assistant minister of Public
Security, held talks with Hui on cross-border criminal activities,
and financial, economic, and other criminal activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
