<HEADLINE> East-West China Cooperation and Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The East-West China Cooperation and
Investment Trade Fair has had some good achievements here, with
305 contracts for a total investment of 3.64 billion yuan signed.
</P>
<P>
According to one local source, the fair had 110 overseas-funded
projects with an investment of more than 560 million US
dollars. The volume of trade hit 3.9 billion yuan, and imports and
exports were worth 219 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A total of 7,000 domestic and overseas business people attended
the fair, whose purpose was to stimulate economic cooperation
between the eastern and western regions of China.
</P>
<P>
The source noted that there is still a great deal of potential
exists for mutual development work by eastern and western
regions. They will benefit each other in resources, land, labor,
and markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
