<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan President Meets Ma Qizhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga today met Ma Qizhi, head of delegation of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and member of the CPC Central
Committee, and had talks with him on bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the Sri Lankan president, who is also
deputy leader of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party (SLFP), spoke highly
of the friendly relations between the two countries and the two
parties, pointing out many common things and cooperation between
the two countries and two parties in economic and cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
She expressed her belief that relations between the two
countries and the two parties will be ever stronger, and hoped
that China will continue to invest in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, Ma Qizhi recalled with admiration the
contributions of the Sri Lankan president and her family to the
friendship between the two countries and the two parties.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan Prime Minister Sirimavo Bandaranaike also met Ma
Qizhi tonight.
</P>
<P>
Ma Qizhi will meet leaders of opposition on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Delegation arrived here on April 5.  
