<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Calls for Resisting Conspirators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina today called upon the people to unitedly resist the
conspirators who are trying to disrupt the ongoing development
process in this country.
</P>
<P>
"Remain vigilant against any evil design of the conspirators
trying to thwart our march towards progress and prosperity," she
told a huge public meeting held here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The public meeting was organized by Hasina's ruling Awami
(people's) League (AL) to deplore attempts by vested groups to
create law and order situation and subversive activities.
</P>
<P>
Seeking all out cooperation from the cheering crowds, the prime
minister said her government would relentlessly work for the
betterment of the people who returned them to power after 21
years.
</P>
<P>
Referring to her government's achievement in the last nine
months, the prime minister said the long outstanding Ganges water
sharing problem with India had been solved and the Chakma refugees
were coming back to their homes.
</P>
<P>
A peaceful agreement on the Chittagong hill tracts insurgency
problem could be reached through negotiations, she added.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hasina also told the crowd that she had invited the
opposition to lead the nation unitedly on the basis of consensus.
</P>
<P>
However, she regretted that whenever her government tried to
solve any problems, her efforts were thwarted by the opposition
Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP), who lost election last June.
</P>
<P>
Referring to her recent call for open dialogue on national
issues with the opposition BNP leader Khaleda Zia, "the door is
still open for dialogue," she claimed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
