<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1600 GMT on April 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS -- Two Mirage 2000 N of the French Air Force crashed into
the Mediterranean Sea at noon Monday, but all the four members of
their crews survived, the Agence France-Presse quoted an air force
source as saying.
</P>
<P>
MOGADISHU -- The first congress by the factions opposing
Hussein Mohamed Aidid in north Mogadishu has endorsed the
convening of a so-called national reconciliation conference in
northeastern port town of Bosasso on June 10 to erect a Somali
government of national unity.
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistani President Farooq Leghari said Monday
that the leadership of Pakistan and India must seek peaceful
resolution of the Kashmir issue for better utilization of human
resources.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan Monday
welcomed the resumption of dialogue between India and Pakistan,
saying that direct talks between the two neighboring countries
were the "right way" to resolve bilateral differences.
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korean parliament Monday opened a series of
hearings on the Hanbo loans scandal which will last 25 days.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Responding to Palestinian President Yasser
Arafat's appeal for help to save the Middle East peace process,
the Non-aligned Movement (NAM) foreign ministers' meeting decided
on Monday to adopt a special declaration expressing the movement's
solidarity with the Palestinian cause, Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- A parcel bomb exploded on Sunday night at the
residence of the Second Secretary of the State Law and Order
Restoration Council of Myanmar Lieutenant-General Tin Oo, killing
the General's eldest daughter, Myanmar authorities confirmed
Monday.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albania decided Sunday to allow a European Union (EU)
mission to expand its activities from the border area to the whole
country, reported Albanian Telegraphic Agency Monday.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's Air Chief Marshal S.K. Sareen said Monday
that the induction of Sukhoi-30 (Su-30) combat jets from Russia
was right on schedule and the first four had reached India.
</P>
