<HEADLINE> German, Spanish Police Smash Drug Trafficking Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- German and Spanish police have
smashed an international drug trafficking ring and seized a total
of 30.5 kilograms of cocaine, according to German police today.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Frankfurt said that police in this
city and in the Spanish capital of Madrid had by last Wednesday
detained all 11 members of the organization, which had been
planning smuggling cocaine from Colombia to Europe.
</P>
<P>
The gang consisted of British nationals, Colombians, an
Austrian and people from other countries.
</P>
<P>
Police began trailing the gang after arresting a British
national in January, who was found trying to carry 10 kilograms of
cocaine from Madrid to Frankfurt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
