<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Car Retailer to List on Botswana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's leading
automobile retailer Mccarthy Retail will dual list on the
Botswana Stock Exchange (BSE) on Tuesday, reported the South
African Press Association from Gaborone, Botswana today.
</P>
<P>
The dual listing, the third on the BSE this year, is expected
to add 1.85 million Pula (about 0.33 million US Dollars) to the
exchange's market capitalization (about four percent) to take it
to 52.3 million Pula (about 9.4 million US Dollars), said the
report.
</P>
<P>
The Mccarthy will list on the BSE more than 160 million
shares, which were trading on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange at
14.6 Rand (about 3.3 US Dollars) on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Mccarthy Group bought control of the Botswana Land Rover
dealership in November last year, making its total investment in
Botswana to 10.8 million US Dollars, the group's largest out of
South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
