<HEADLINE> Italian President Meets Chinese NPC Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro said today that his country will never change its policy
of developing friendly relations and cooperation with China in
spite of frequent changes of its government.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC) Chairman Qiao Shi, he praised China's economic achievements
and said it was a common consensus among the Italian people and
business community to develop friendly ties with China.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi said that China attaches great importance to
developing friendly relations and cooperation with Italy.
</P>
<P>
Since China and Italy established diplomatic relations in 1970,
the relationship between the two has developed smoothly, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, the exchange visits of top leaders
between the two countries had become more frequent, while cultural
exchanges had increased and economic ties strengthened.
</P>
<P>
There had been frequent exchanges between the Chinese NPC and
the Italian parliament, he added.
</P>
<P>
There was a bright prospect for the relationship and
cooperation, Qiao added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
