<HEADLINE> Foreign Ships Operating in Mozambican Seas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Foreign vessels have been
operating illegally in the seas of Mozambique since last year,
the Mozambique Information Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The illegal activities of these foreign vessels, mainly from
South Africa and Madagascar, took place in the Angoche seas of
Nampula Province in northern Mozambique under coordination from
Mozambicans or companies, local residents said.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities, who knows the situation well, has not taken
any measure to solve this problem, the residents complained to
Minister of Agriculture and Fishery Carlos Agostinho who is
visiting there, the agency said. 
</P>
