<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Taiwan, Hong Kong Industrialists (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qian said that direct shipping across the Taiwan Straits is a
matter of common concern. This will benefit contracts and
exchanges, help them increase mutual understanding, eliminate
differences, reach a consensus, and promote economic relations,
trade, and common prosperity, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We have been unremitting in our efforts to this end," he said.
</P>
<P>
Last August, he said, the Ministry of Communications and the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation announced
management methods for direct shipping, and defined the principle
of "one China" and the meaning of two-way direct shipping and
mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
This not only safeguards shipping interests across the Taiwan
Straits but also benefits economic cooperation and trade, helping
to promote direct mail exchanges and direct trade and air
transport, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted that from ancient times, Xiamen has been regarded as
an important bridge across the Taiwan Straits, and since 1979, it
has done its part in promoting economic exchanges and cooperation
across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Last year, he said, the Xiamen harbor was declared a trial site
for direct shipping, and this year, the first export commodity
fair is being held in Xiamen, providing a chance for direct
cooperation between Taiwan business people and mainland firms.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed the belief that the fair will be fully
successful, with the support of compatriots across the Taiwan
Straits, and will contribute to the peaceful reunification of the
motherland. 
</P>
