<HEADLINE> EU Not to Put Forth Anti-China Proposal in Geneva </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NOORDWIJK, the Netherlands, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Dutch Foreign
Minister Hans van Mierlo said here today that the European Union
(EU) will not put forward a proposal to censer China's human
rights record in the U.N. Commission on Human Rights.
</P>
<P>
Van Mierlo told reporters that no such proposal will be made in
Geneva since France has refused to participate and its stand won
support from Germany, Italy and Spain.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the 15 EU members discussed the issue
in Noordwijk on Sunday, but they failed to reach an agreement till
midnight, he said.
</P>
<P>
Under EU's rules of unanimity, the EU won't be able to put
forth a proposal against China this year, said the foreign
minister, whose country is holding the EU rotating presidency.
</P>
<P>
With the support of the United States, EU has for six
consecutive years presented anti-China proposals in the
commission, but all the efforts were foiled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
