<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Islamic Militants Massacre 101 People in 4 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Algeria's Islamic militants killed
101 villagers from last Thursday to Sunday in an atrocious
terrorist campaign launched two months before the legislative
elections to be held in the country, said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen people had their throats cut Sunday in Ain Lehdid, 65
kilometers from the village of Tiaret southwest of Algiers, and 13
shepherds were kidnapped in the El-Gaada forest of the same region
Saturday by an armed group of Islamic militants, reported the
Algerian daily Liberte today.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed in a monastery in Sidi Abdelkrim near
Saida by a group of Islamic militants. The victims was the chief
of the monastery and his nephew, reported the Algerian daily El
Watan today.
</P>
<P>
Islamic militants killed 84 other people, sometimes with chain
saw, in several mid-night raids upon villages in the center of the
country Thursday and Friday, reported Algerian papers Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The most atrocious massacre took place Thursday night in the
hamlet village of Thalit, near Medea 80 kilometers south of
Algiers, where 52 people, including women, children and the
elderly, had their throats cut by a commando of 30 to 40 Islamic
militants.
</P>
<P>
Nine other people were killed and seven people kidnapped by
Islamic militants in their attacks upon two other villages in the
same province.
</P>
<P>
In Amroussa, a small village in the plain of Matidja, about 15
people had their throats cut and heads chopped off with chain saw
by Islamic militants headed by Antar Zouabri, the feared chief of
the militant group of Armed Islamic Group, Friday night.
</P>
<P>
In the same night, an armed group of Iswlamic militants
attacked a farm in M'ridja, near the seaside resort of
Sidi-Ferruch, 25 kilometers west of Algiers, killing four people.
</P>
<P>
An army barrack was reportedly only located 200 meters from the
site where the killing took place.
</P>
<P>
In the region of Bouira east of Algiers, four people were
killed Thursday on a road between Ain Bessem and Beni Slimane.
</P>
<P>
The massacres took place when Algerian security forces are
launching a heavy anti-terrorist operation against the Islamic
militants since early February in the southwestern regions of
Medea, Saida and Sidi Bel Abbes, and the western region of
Tlemcen.
</P>
<P>
Although the Algerian government has provided no specific
figures of casualties from the operation, Algerian papers said that
a large number of Islamists have been killed.
</P>
<P>
In a recent attack upon an Islamic stronghold in Kabylie, 100
kilometers east of Algiers, about 100 Islamic militants were
killed by the security forces who were backed by military
helicopters, reported El Watan.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic militants, estimated at several thousand, use
heavily mined mountains, caves and forests as their bases to fend
off the attacks by government forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
