<HEADLINE> Swaziland Plagued by Over Population, AIDS: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Swaziland's Finance Minister
Themba Masuku today said population explosion is a major problem
affecting economic growth of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Southern African Broadcasting Association (SABA) quoted
Masuku as saying Swaziland's population grows at 3.1 percent a
year while the economic growth in the country only registers 2.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Economic Association of Swaziland, Masuku also
pointed out that the increasing number of people infected with
AIDS is another great threat to the country.
</P>
<P>
So far 19 percent of pregnant women in Swaziland have the HIV
virus which causes AIDS, Masuku said.
</P>
<P>
Swaziland, bordering with South Africa and Mozambique, has a
population of about 900,000 in an area of 17,363 sq km. 
</P>
