<HEADLINE> Gunmen Rob Bosnian Bus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Two unidentified gunmen today
attacked a bus on the highway between Sarajevo and Gorazde, said
reports.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen entered the bus when it stopped by the roadside to
place chains on the tires because it was snowing, and forced the
driver to continue driving so that they could rob passengers.
</P>
<P>
Six hundred German marks were stolen from drivers and
passengers, with some of them beaten on head by the robbers who
ran away when the bus approached a police checkpoint.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, Bosnian authorities urged the NATO-led
Stablization Force to undertake actions to ensure safe travel on
highways in Bosnia, the reports said. 
