<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Attend Meeting on Meat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe is one of several African
countries which will attend a major regional meeting to discuss
the future of the meat industry in Namibia next month.
</P>
<P>
The Brussels-based Center for the Development of Industry
(CDI) said in a statement the meeting will, among other issues,
propose how regional players can increase their export market
share.
</P>
<P>
About 40 entrepreneurs from Ethiopia, Kenya, Tanzania,
Botswana, Namibia, Swaziland, Zimbabwe and the European Union are
expected to attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
European participants are being selected largely on their
capacity to respond to the needs and requirements of the African
companies visited during the survey, both as potential buyers
and/or technical partners.
</P>
<P>
The May 26 to 30 meeting will also explore possibilities of
establishing viable and lasting business relations between
European and African entrepreneurs in the meat sector, the
organizers said.
</P>
<P>
The CDI said the meat sector in Africa had in the past few
years undergone considerable changes which called for a
strengthening of business relations between European and African
companies. 
</P>
