<HEADLINE> Mediterranean Parliamentarians Conference Ends in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Speakers of the Mediterranean
parliaments ended their two-day conference here today with a
decision to institutionalize a permanent Mediterranean
parliamentary forum.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after the conference today, Greek
Parliament Speaker Apostolos Kaklamanis, who made the proposal,
said that the participants also decided to take actions in order
to consolidate the democratic institutions, human rights respect,
inter-cultural dialogue, and battle against organized crime,
racism and illegal migration.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for substantial dialogue between the
Mediterranean parliaments, the necessity to stick to the Barcelona
Declaration for Euro-Mediterranean cooperation, the need to
establish a free trade zone in the Mediterranean and the will to
create a Mediterranean peace, stability and development zone.
</P>
<P>
The conference strongly supported the European Union (EU)
initiatives to assist Albania to return to normality as soon as
possible, he added.
</P>
<P>
The conference, attended by 17 Mediterranean parliaments
speakers, took place here on Sunday with the aim of exploring ways
to upgrade the roles of national parliaments in the course towards
European unification and the promotion of the Mediterranean region
as one of peace for Europe. 
</P>
