<HEADLINE> UNDP Launches Information Network for Small Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
United Nations, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) today announced the formation of the
Small Island Developing States Network, a global information
network for small islands.
</P>
<P>
Aimed at helping small islands exchange and gain information on
sustainable development and the environment, the effort is a
follow-up activity of the 1994 Conference on Small Island
Developing States in Barbados, according to UNDP.
</P>
<P>
As many as 43 small island countries could benefit by receiving
the technology and training needed to participate in the internet
program, UNDP reported.
</P>
<P>
The small island countries face a range of environmental and
resource challenges, including the threat of rising sea levels,
declining water tables, increasing pollution and energy
limitations, UNDP added. 
</P>
