<HEADLINE> 40 Million Ethiopians Live in Malaria Prone Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- About 40 million Ethiopians
live in malaria prone areas as 1.5 million people are annually
infected by the disease.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed at a meeting today organized by the
Ethiopian Ministry of Health to mark the World Health Day which
falls on today.
</P>
<P>
According to the meeting, only one third of those affected by
the disease get treatment at health institutions.
</P>
<P>
Malaria was reported last year as the second killer disease
after tuberculosis in the African country.
</P>
<P>
Malaria surfaces twice a year as epidemic in Ethiopia in the
months of September, October and November as well as April, May
and June. the disease attacks people of all age groups. 
</P>
