Northern Ireland's war-weary people want the next British
government to push ahead with the dead-locked Northern Ireland
peace process, but almost all the people polled are pessimistic
about the all-party peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The poll by Belfast's Queen's University revealed that 94
percent of the province's 1.5 million people supported the peace
talks on the future of Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
But 74 percent of the people surveyed doubted that the peace
talks would lead to a negotiated settlement of a 28-year conflict
which has killed 3,200 people. 
