<HEADLINE> Zaire Rebels Take Kipushi Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the Alliance of
Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo-Zaire (ADFL) today
took the town of Kipushi on the Zambian border before dawn, a
report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
A force of at least several hundred rebel troops swept through
Kipushi just 30 kilometers west of the crucial mining center and
second largest city of Lubumbashi, capital of Shaba province, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The Lubumbashi headquarters of the Gecamines Mining Company
decided to shut up shop, pushing up cobalt prices in European
trading.
</P>
<P>
Airlines cancelled all flights to Lubumbashi as a precaution
in the city.
</P>
<P>
This happened at a time when Zaire peace talks were held in
South Africa without any results because the rebels insist that
President Mobutu Sese Seko quit power before cease-fire is
realized.
</P>
<P>
The rebels took up arms to fight last October and seized
Kisangani, the third largest city of Zaire in late March after
smashing an offensive launched by government troops.
</P>
<P>
They are now advancing along the road toward Lubumbashi and
have vowed to capture Kinshasa in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
