<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Petroleum Enterprise Incurs Loss </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Petroleum
Enterprise has incurred a loss of 30 million Birr (about 4.5
million Dollars) during the last six months, Ethiopian Trade
Minister Kassahun Ayele said today.
</P>
<P>
In a statement on the recent price adjustment on petroleum,
the minister ascribed the loss to last September's price
adjustment which, he said, was not leveled according to the
world market.
</P>
<P>
As government property, the enterprise had only to sell its
products at a fixed price and had been subsidized by the
government until the recent adjustment in the price of petroleum,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The enterprise might have been liquidated, had it not been for
the subsidy it used to obtain previously, he said, adding that
the recent price regulation, it is hoped, will enable it to
function at least on a loss-free basis.
</P>
<P>
The government adjusted prices of petroleum products on March
27, 1997 and said it will adjust petroleum prices every six
months.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is an oil import country. It imported 235 million
Dollars of oil and petroleum products in 1995/96. 
</P>
</TEXT>
