<HEADLINE> Cameroun: 74 Parties Intend to Run in Legislative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-four political parties in
Cameroun have so far indicated their intention to run in the
upcoming legislative elections settled for May 17, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the Ministry of Territorial Administration said as
the deadline for the deposition of lists of constituencies was
due on April 3, no more parties are expected to attend.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, today is also the deadline for the deposition of
the lists of candidates by the political parties at the senior
divisional offices of their various constituencies.
</P>
<P>
A list of candidates shall be made out in a nomination paper
in three copies bearing the legalized signature of candidate not
more than 40 days before the election day and before the normal
office closing hours.
</P>
<P>
Administrative authorities will from tomorrow have seven days
to verify that their candidates are in conformity with the law.
</P>
<P>
Political parties are still called upon to present their party
emblems and characteristics at the Ministry of the Territorial
Administration so as to facilitate the printing of the ballot
papers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
