<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Bull Market in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Stock trading in Shanghai was
strong in March amidst optimistic market sentiment and good
corporate results, with the daily volume jumping nearly 40 percent
over February.
</P>
<P>
Active trading was the start of a new bull market, analysts
said. The Shanghai Composite Stock Index rose 18.68 percent in the
past month, to close at 1,234.62. The blue chip SSE-30 stock
index soared 21.24 percent, to 3,418.28.
</P>
<P>
"The strong market was supported by favorable year-end
corporate results, and blue chips showed extremely brilliant
performance," said a local stock analyst.
</P>
<P>
The B stock market for foreign investors also rallied in the
past month, with the B share index closing at 73.53 at the end of
March, up almost ten percent from February.
</P>
<P>
The treasury bond market was brisk during the period with a
monthly volume of 190.225 billion yuan, more than double the
volume of February.
</P>
<P>
Prices of funds also rose, with the monthly trading volume
almost trebling the previous month, at more than three billion
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
