<HEADLINE> 12th NAM Ministerial Meeting Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The two-day 12th Ministerial
Conference of Non-aligned Movement (NAM) countries ended here
today by adopting a series of documents on issues including U.N.
reforms, environment protection and the Middle East peace.
</P>
<P>
In the Special Declaration on the Middle East Peace Process
adopted today, the ministers called on NAM countries to freeze
relations with Israel at their current level and use all available
measures to ensure Israel's compliance with all the commitments it
has made during the Middle East peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which opened here on Monday, also decided that
South Africa will take over the NAM chairmanship from Colombia at
the 12th NAM summit scheduled to be held in that African country
next year.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers from about 70 countries took part in the
event. U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan and Palestinian President
Yasser Arafat were also present on the first day of the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
