<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Proposes Euro-Asian Alliance for CIS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev said here today that an "Euro-Asian alliance" will be
the best model for the integration of the Commonwealth of the
Independent States (CIS).
</P>
<P>
"The Integration in the CIS on various levels and with
different paces should be built on the basis of respecting each
other's sovereignty and territorial integrity, and of mutual
benefit in trade," Nazarbayev told a joint press conference after
talks with visiting Kyrgyz President Askar Akayevich Akayev.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the Russia-Belarus Union which was formed last
Wednesday, Nazarbayev said it was a new model in CIS integration.
</P>
<P>
He said the model might provide a new experience of integration
for other CIS countries, but Kazakhstan would wait to see its
development.
</P>
<P>
Akayev voiced support for Nazarbayev's idea of an Euro-Asian
Alliance, and said his country held the same stance as Kazakhstan
on CIS integration.
</P>
<P>
After their talks today, the two presidents signed a treaty on
permanent friendship, and 18 agreements and protocols on
investment, avoidance of double taxation, and on cooperation in
science, technology and military affairs,
</P>
<P>
Akayev and his delegation, including his prime minister and
parliament leaders, arrived in Alma Ata earlier today for a
two-day visit to Kazakstan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
