<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Extends Trade Privileges for Andean Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NOORDWIJK, the Netherlands, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The European
Union (EU) decided today to extend trade privileges for five
Andean countries, and promised to increase its investment in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The generalized system of preference (GSP), trade privileges,
on agricultural and fishery products would remain in force for the
five countries indefinitely, said a statement following a meeting
of EU foreign ministers with their counterparts of Bolivia,
Colombia, Ecuador, Peru and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The GSP privileges have been granted mainly to encourage the
replacement of narcotic-drug production with food farming.
</P>
<P>
Owing to the GSP privileges, the statement said, there had been
an increase in business opportunities for investors from both the
EU and Latin America.
</P>
<P>
The EU's troika -- the foreign ministers of the last, the
current and next presidents of the 15-nation bloc -- were meeting
Andean Pact nations on the periphery of a EU-Latin America
Ministerial Conference now under way in the Dutch seaside town of
Noordwijk. 
</P>
</TEXT>
