<HEADLINE> Eastern Art From France To Be Displayed in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A valuable selection of Chinese
art, usually displayed only in Paris galleries, will be shipped to
Hong Kong for public viewing as from the end of the month.
</P>
<P>
Enamels, porcelains, paintings and engravings, among a variety
of art treasures dated from the 2nd century BC to the 18th
century, will be on display at the Hong Kong Museum of Art.
</P>
<P>
Entitled "From Beijing to Versailles: Artistic Relations
Between China and France," the exhibition will be the museum's
first attempt to feature the cultural and art exchange between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The exhibits are mostly selected from the Musee National des
Arts Asiatiques -- the Guimet Museum, one of the largest museums
of Asian art in the world.
</P>
<P>
The event is jointly organized by the Hong Kong Urban Council
and the Consulate General of France in the territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
