<HEADLINE> Tajik Peace Talks to Open in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A new round of Tajik peace talks
will open here Wednesday with the participation of Gerd Dietrich
Merriam, U.N. Secretary General's special envoy on Tajikistan
affairs, the English daily Iran News reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the peace talks will be attended by
Tajik Foreign Minister Talabak Nazarov and acting opposition
leader Akbar Turajonzoda.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati will also attend
the meeting, which will focus on the delineation of the future
political system of Tajikistan. The two sides from Tajikistan are
expected to sign a document to the effect, according to the
report.
</P>
<P>
Several rounds of official and unofficial Tajik peace talks
have been held in the Iranian capital of Iran, Moscow and
Ashkhabad of Russia, and Islamabad of Pakistan to date.
This is the third time for Tehran to host such talks.
</P>
<P>
The previous round of talks between the two sides was
held in Tehran on October 26, which prepared grounds for a
meeting between President Emomali Rakhmanov and Abullah Nouri, the
leader of the Opposition.
</P>
<P>
In the forthcoming meeting, the representatives of observer
countries, including Russia and the neighboring countries of
Tajikistan, will be present, the daily disclosed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
