COLOMBO, April 8 (Xinhua) -- At Least four persons were
arrested and 32 repeater guns were seized by police during their
raids in Colombo today, according to official radio here tonight.
</P>
<P>
The radio said that police today arrested four persons and
seized a stock of 32 repeater guns hidden underground in a
building on Kuppiyawatte Road, Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The guns were well greased, separately covered in polythene and
 hidden in a specially constructed underground concrete
compartment.
</P>
<P>
A special police team has been deployed to search the premises
for more weapons and to ascertain whether some of them have been
removed, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
These suspects are being questioned, the radio quoted a senior
police officer as saying.  
</P>
</TEXT>
