<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Budget for Setting Up HKSAR Government Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) Chief Executive's Office (CE's Office)
 announced here today the budget estimate required for the setting
 up of the SAR government.
</P>
<P>
The total estimated provision is 107.8 million HK dollars (13.8
 million US dollars), covering the estimated budget for the CE's
Office, the SAR Executive Council and the Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC).
</P>
<P>
"In drawing up the budget, we have taken into account the
expenses incurred since December 16, 1996 (when Tung Chee Hwa was
officially appointed the CE) and the anticipated expenses for the
period up to June 30, 1997," a spokesman for the office said.
</P>
<P>
The total estimated provision for the CE and his office is 49.4
 million HK dollars (6.3 million US dollars), comprising the
estimated provision for salary and related provision, and
operating expenses.
</P>
<P>
About 3 million HK dollars (385,000 US dollars) and 42.4
million HK dollars (5.4 million US dollars) have been set aside as
 honorarium for members of the SAR Executive Council and the PLC
respectively.
</P>
<P>
After consulting the Secretariat to the PLC, the CE's Office
has made a provision of 13 million HK dollars (1.7 million US
dollars) to cover the operating expenses for the Secretariat up to
 June 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Of the total estimated requirement, around 36.4 million HK
dollars (4.7 million US dollars), or one-third, will be met by the
 Hong Kong government while the rest, around 71.4 million HK
dollars (9.2 million US dollars), will be paid for by an advance
from the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
"The Central People's Government (CPG) provides the advance on
an interest-free basis," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"We manage the budget in accordance with established financial
regulations and the principle of prudence," the spokesman
said. "We shall give a full account of the actual expenses
incurred for setting up the SAR government and seek approval for
reimbursement of expenses to the CPG as soon as possible after
July 1, 1997."  
</P>
</TEXT>
