<HEADLINE> Education Becomes Billion-Dollar Export Industry For </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Education has become a
billion-dollar export industry for Australia, as in 1995-96
120,000 overseas students studying in the country had brought in
600 million Australian dollars (about 450 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Additional benefits came from their contribution to teaching
and research, future trade opportunities and tourism by their
relatives and friends, the Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS)
said in a bulletin today.
</P>
<P>
"The export of education is one of the major success stories of
the Australian service sector in recent years, generating earnings
of more than one billion Australian dollars (780 million US
dollars) annually," the ABS said.
</P>
<P>
Most of the students came from the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The students regarded Australia as an easily accessible country
which provides high-quality, internationally recognized education
at a lower cost than the US, the ABS said.  
</P>
