<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 8 (Xinhua) -- In another sign indicating the
deterioration of relations with the Palestinians, Israel today
did not allow the Palestinian Council members to travel from
Gaza to Ramallah in the West Bank for a weekly meeting.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Queria (Abu Ala), President of the legislative
Palestinian Council, said that "there is no logic in the world
which justified the government of Israel to reach this level of
insolence and arrogance," according to a report of JMCC, a
Palestinian press service based in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
