<HEADLINE> China Downs S. Korea in Semifinals of Asian Junior Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Both Chinese boy's and girls teams
entered the finals by overwhelming South Korean and Japanese
opponents here Tuesday in the first Asian Junior Badminton
Championship.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese players swept their South Korean rivals 3-0 in the
boys' semifinals. Top-seeded Xia Xuanze beat South Korea's Kwon
Woo-jin 15-0, 15-2, Chen Hong routed Choo Kyo-geon 15-2, 15-1, and
Zhang Yi beat Chun Sae-po 15-2, 15-3.
</P>
<P>
In the doubles, Xia and Chen downed Heo Hyeong-seon and Chun
Dong-chul 15-8, 15-5, and Cheng Rui and Jian Shan completed the
sweep by winning 15-3, 15-6 against Kwon and Choo.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese girls crushed their Japanese opponents in both
singles and doubles.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese boys will play the winner of a semifinal between
Malaysia and Indonesia, while the girls will meet the winner
between South Korea and Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The championships also includes teams from Singapore, Iran,
Macau, India, the Philippines, Vietnam, Pakistan, Cambodia, Nepal,
Burma, Bangladesh, Kazakstan and Syria. 
</P>
