<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Urges Greater China-US Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua, meeting
with a delegation from the US's Exxon Corporation in Beijing
today, led by vice-president R.E. Wilhelm, expressed his
appreciation for the company's long-term cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government is very attentive to
petrochemical industry developments because it is one of the
pillar sectors of the national economy.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Exxon is one of the world's best-known
petrochemical corporations and that the China Petrochemical
Corporation (Sinopec) is one of the most powerful in China.
Cooperation between the two giants is beneficial in using each
other's strong points.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier told the American guests that China, which is
developing its economy with its own force, is also seeking foreign
cooperation and support. He said he advocates this kind of
cooperation, combining foreign technology and capital with China's
resources, manpower, and huge market.
</P>
<P>
Wilhelm said that Exxon has had economic links with China for
over 100 years. Since the 1980s, it has actively participated in
China's energy development, including oil and gas exploration,
development and transportation, electricity generation, and
marketing of oil and chemical products.
</P>
<P>
Zou expressed his appreciation for the cooperation between
Exxon and Sinopec and Fujian Province in a huge refinery and
chemical project there, and urged both sides to expand the
long-term cooperation on the basis of mutual benefit and equal
development.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the meeting were Vice-Minister of the State
Planning Commission Ye Qing and President of the China
Petrochemical Corporation Sheng Huaren. 
</P>
</TEXT>
