<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Gov't Ministries to Charge Each Other for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Singapore government ministries
and agencies will, in the next one or two years, start charging
each other for selected support services that are now provided
free, Finance Minister Richard Hu said today.
</P>
<P>
He said that by establishing a buyer-seller relationship
between ministries, it would cultivate a "customer service"
mindset among the departments.
</P>
<P>
It would also allow resources to be better used by discouraging
the tendency to over consume when services were free of charge, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The finance minister said this to reporters when he
commissioned 102 ministries and government departments as
autonomous agencies (AA).
</P>
<P>
Other initiatives include making the AAs pay the rental of
their premises, including government-owned ones. This, Hu said,
would encourage prudence when choosing the location and size of
office space.
</P>
<P>
These changes are important in reforming the civil service to
one with the best conditions for Singapore to succeed, the finance
minister said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
