<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 12:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Iranians Die of Heart Attack Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A total of 18,674 people died of
coronary heart disease in the Iranian capital of Tehran during
the last Iranian calendar year which ended on March 20, 1997,
local Persian daily Iran reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the number of heart-related deaths showed
an increase of 5.3 percent last year over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Specialists ascribed the increasing number of heart diseases
to much consumption of oil and stress of work and life due to
economic hardship in the country.
</P>
<P>
Some 50 percent of all deaths in Tehran during the past
Iranian year were related to heart or coronary complications.
</P>
<P>
The number of deaths last year rose by 1.5 percent or 1,134
more compared with that of the previous year,
according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
