<HEADLINE> US Forces in Gulf Put on High Alert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. forces in the Gulf
region have been put on high alert in anticipation of new
terrorist attacks, the United Arab Emirates (UAE) newspaper
Al-Ittihad reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted a U.S. Navy spokesman as saying Monday in the
Bahraini capital of Manama that the security measures include
restricting the disembarkation of 12,000 seamen from the warships
operating in the Gulf and forbidding their entry into
Bahraini restaurants until further notice.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman revealed that the U.S. embassy in Bahrain and
the U.S. Army have got word of likely terrorist actions against
the U.S. forces in the region.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 U.S. soldiers were killed in two bombings in
Saudi Arabia in November 1995 and in June last year. 
