<HEADLINE> FIDE's World Championships Venues Announces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The World Chess Federation (FIDE)
championship will be played at two venues -- Groeningen in the
Netherlands and either Lausanne, Switzerland or Elista in Russia,
FIDE president Kirsan Ilyumzhinov announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The championships will be held from December 16, 1997 to
January 8, 1998, with Groeningen serving as the venue for the
rounds up to the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The semi-finals and final will take place either at Lausanne or
at Elista.
</P>
<P>
Last year Ilyumzhinov forwarded a plan that annual world
championships should be organized and the event last for two weeks
over the Christmas period, consisting of a knock-out tournament as
in tennis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
