<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Per Capita GDP Above 20,000 Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Per capita Gross Domestic Product
(GDP) in Shanghai was 22,086 yuan (about 2,600 US dollars) last
year, according to the Municipal Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The figure represents an increase of 3,143 yuan from the
previous year, and makes the municipality one of the best
performers in terms of per capita GDP, bureau officials say.
</P>
<P>
It also means that Shanghai has caught up with the world's
middle income level countries in per capita GDP, analysts say.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's economy experienced a strong take-off in the
early '90s, with GDP growth outpacing the national average in the
past five years. The GDP increased 13 percent on an annual basis
last year, to 287.7 billion yuan, almost 4.3 times 1980's figure.
</P>
<P>
China's national GDP growth was 9.7 percent last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
