<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 13:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 14 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in the operations
launched by the Turkish government troops in southeastern Turkey,
an official statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the government troops wiped out 13 PKK militants
in the armed clashes in Batman province, which started two days
ago, and one in Bingol province.
</P>
<P>
One officer of the Turkish security forces also died in the
clashes in Gercus town of Batman with the PKK guerrillas, said
the statement.
</P>
<P>
It added that the operations against the PKK are continuing
in this region.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 12-year-old separatist war for
autonomy, which has claimed more than 21,000 lives in eastern
and southeastern Turkey since August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
