<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Steady Industrial Growth in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China has seen a steady increase
in industrial output in the first quarter, according to a monthly
report on the country's industrial production released by the
State Statistics Bureau (SSB) today.
</P>
<P>
It said that in the January-March period, the country's
industry above the township-level had an output value of 452.5
billion yuan, an increase of 11 percent over the same period of
last year, when adjusted for inflation.
</P>
<P>
There is a growing trend in industrial production, the report
said, which last March jumped to 13.5 percent, a sharp rise
compared with the average of 10.4 percent in January and February.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter, the output value increased 6.8 percent in
the state-owned sector and in enterprises controlled by the state,
while foreign-funded and other enterprises registered 14.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country's light and heavy industries developed in harmony
with each other during the January-March period, with the product
mix improving.
</P>
<P>
Added value in light industry stood at 190.3 billion yuan, up
11.2 percent from the same period of 1996. That for heavy industry
was 262.2 billion yuan, representing an increase of 10.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The report shows that production of durable consumer goods like
color televisions, radios, cameras, washing machines,
refrigerators, and air-conditioners saw a big increase in the
first quarter, with growth rates ranging from 12.7 percent to 33.6
percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970408.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Industrial Growth in China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Energy and major raw materials output saw a comparatively
smooth increase, while sharp increases were reported in building
materials and products for agricultural use.
</P>
<P>
Industrial sales saw a slight increase, averaging 93.96
percent, up 0.85 percentage points from the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The light industrial sector reported sales of 93.53 percent, an
increase of 1.12 percentage points over the corresponding 1996
period, while that of heavy industry was 94.3 percent, up 0.63
percentage points.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey by the bureau of 360,000 domestic
enterprises, there was upward momentum in profits in the
industry. The composite index for industry in the January-February
period stood at 77.35 points, up 1.21 percentage points over the
same period of last year, while Chinese enterprises had 7.08
billion yuan in profits, a slight rebound of 0.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the SSB monthly report says that existing problems and
difficulties of the industry, especially bottlenecks in production
and management and increasing losses in the state-owned sector,
are far from being solved, in spite of a series of "positive
changes" in the country's industrial operations in the first
quarter.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the structural readjustment efforts should
be increased in the industrial sector, and that reforms in
state-owned enterprises should be accelerated for greater progress
in "operation quality" in the industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
