<HEADLINE> DPRK Agrees In Principle to S.Korean Trade Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK) has agreed in principle to South Korea's proposal for
opening a trade office in a free trade area.
</P>
<P>
The office is expected to be set up in the DPRK's Rajin Sonbong
free trade zone within this year, said Hong Ji-son, head of the
semi-official Korea Trade Investment and Promotion Agency (KOTRA)
in Seoul.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Hong met officials of the DPRK's Committee for
Promotion of External Economic Cooperation during his eight-day
visit to Pyongyang, and held talks on the trade office proposal.
</P>
<P>
Following Hong's further proposal to send five KOTRA staff to
the trade office, DPRK officials failed to give an immediate
reply, saying they needed time to ponder it.
</P>
<P>
However, KOTRA predicted it would be able to establish the
office in the free trade area in June, in view of recent warming
of DPRK-United States relations.
</P>
<P>
Hong said he also proposed a trade fair in the zone in the
second half of this year and received an affirmative reply from
the DPRK. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
