<HEADLINE> Blackmailer Poisons German Food Maker's Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Products of the German food
manufacturer, Thomy GmbH, sold in Germany have been poisoned by
unknown blackmailers who have pressed for several million dollars,
police announced today.
</P>
<P>
A supermarket in the western German city of Saarbruecken was
closed by local police authorities Monday after a mustard tube was
found poisoned with a deadly dose of cyanide.
</P>
<P>
Another supermarket in the northern port city of Bremen was
also closed by police the same day.
</P>
<P>
Police authorities urgently warned customers today who had
bought Thomy products after April 1 at the two supermarkets, and
another in the southern city of Regensburg, not to consume them
for precautionary reasons.
</P>
<P>
A Frankfurt police spokesman told the German press that a
blackmailer threatened to poison Thomy products for the first time
several months ago in Frankfurt, followed by several other threats
targeting certain supermarkets in Munich and some other locations
in the state of Bavaria.
</P>
<P>
Police, however, found no poisoned food at those supermarkets.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
