<DOCNO> XIE19970408.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Sowing Area to Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China's sowing area this year will
increase by 1.6 million ha, or 1.05 percent, over last year,
according to the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said the sowing area will total 153 million ha this
year.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the planting area for grain, oil-bearing crops,
and sugar crops will increase while that for cotton, linen, and
medicinal crops will decrease.
</P>
<P>
The southern part of the country will witness increasing sowing
area and the northern part decreasing.
</P>
<P>
The bureau attributed the change to the southern parts'
attention to agricultural production, especially grain
production. The northern provinces, suffering from monoculture and
lower grain prices, cut their grain planting area this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the bureau, the grain planting area in the country
will reach 112.55 million ha this year, up 0.36 percent from last
year, with summer grain area rising by 2.67 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
