<HEADLINE> Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration Fruitful: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-Portuguese Joint
Declaration on the Question of Macao, which was signed 10 years
ago, has yielded positive results under the friendly cooperation
between China and Portugal, a senior Chinese official said today.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch,
said in an interview with Xinhua that the joint declaration bears
"significant historical and immediate importance" and is being
carried out seriously by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
"The joint declaration has been implemented over the past ten
years under the friendly cooperation between China and Portugal,"
said the director.
</P>
<P>
"Under the frame of the declaration, progress has been made in
the latter period of Macao's transition.
</P>
<P>
The declaration is very helpful to the preparation for the
establishment of a special administrative region (SAR)."
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, the declaration has played an
"encouraging role in Macao's economic growth and social
stability."
</P>
<P>
Signed on April 13, 1987, the declaration says that China will
resume its exercise of sovereignty over Macao as of December 20,
1999, and that Macao's capitalist system and basic life style will
remain unchanged for 50 years.
</P>
<P>
"The successful settlement of the Macao issue has ushered the
friendly ties between the governments and peoples of the two
countries in a new stage," he said.
</P>
<P>
The signing of the joint declaration was a major event in the
history of China.
</P>
<P>
He said "Macao will enter into a new prosperous period under
the principles of 'one country, two systems,' a high degree of
autonomy and 'Macao people governing Macao.'"
</P>
<P>
"The best way to commemorate the 10th anniversary of the joint
declaration is to well-handle two major tasks in Macao -- one is
to keep Macao's economy growing and society stable, and the other
is to prepare for the establishment of the future Macao SAR
government," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he is confident that the two tasks will be fulfilled
through further cooperation between the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
