<HEADLINE> EU Discussion on Hong Kong Statement Inappropriate: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Shen Guofang told a press conference here today that the
European Union's discussion of a statement on the Hong Kong issue
is "inappropriate" and that China cannot accept interference in
its internal affairs in the matter.
</P>
<P>
Before July 1, Shen said, the Hong Kong issue is "a matter
between the Chinese and British governments," and will be China's
internal affair afterwards.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese Government has all along acted in
accordance with the Sino-British Joint Declaration and the Basic
Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), and
that after Hong Kong's return the Chinese Government will
safeguard the democratic rights and freedom of Hong Kong citizens
and will protect other countries' legitimate rights and interests
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"We hope the EU will try to understand Hong Kong's real
situation and China's policy toward Hong Kong, and do the
necessary study of the matter," Shen said.
</P>
<P>
He said the EU should not listen to the words of other people
that contradict reality and should not follow some people in
"playing the international card" on the Hong Kong issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
