<HEADLINE> Beijing Sees Sharp Increase in GSM Subscribers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Over the past two years, 200,000
people in Beijing have become subscribers to GSM (global service
for mobile communication), an official with the Beijing Posts and
Telecommunications Bureau said.
</P>
<P>
The GSM network was launched in Beijing in April 1995, and the
number of such mobile phone users is twice that in cellular phone
network during the past decade, according to Zhao Jidong,
vice-director of the bureau.
</P>
<P>
Digital mobile phones are popular because of their high-quality
and secret communication and strong resistance against
interference, Zhao said.
</P>
<P>
At present, the network's capacity in Beijing is 300,000
handsets, and by the end of this year, the figure is expected to
reach 500,000.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing network has been linked up with 1,173 counties and
cities across the country, as well as countries and regions
including Singapore, Finland, Germany, Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
</TEXT>
