<HEADLINE> Cholera Kills 85 People in East Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 8 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of cholera has killed
85 persons in east Nigeria's Cross River State since the
beginning of this year, the Punch newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report named Bokki, Ikot-Ana, Union Island, Abia, Etung,
Ikom as the worst hit areas.
</P>
<P>
It quoted local residents as attributing the epidemics to the
lack of potable water, saying that many people get their drinking
water from polluted stream.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the National Electric Power Authority
in Cross River had cut off its power supply to the State Water
Board which is responsible for the supply of water, as the later
owes it a large sum of money.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper also indicated the lack of proper attention and
medical treatment of the patients due to the shortage of medical
facilities and expensive medicines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
