<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Unemployment Down in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Germany's unemployment fell to 4.47
million, or 11.7 percent, in March from a postwar record high in
February of 4.67 million, or 12.2 percent, showed official figures
released today.
</P>
<P>
About 194,700 fewer people were jobless last month. In western
Germany, joblessness dropped by 130,000 to about 3.12 million
while in eastern part of the country, unemployment declined by
64,700 to nearly 1.35 million.
</P>
<P>
Bernhard Jagoda, chief of the Federal Labour Office, said the
improvement in the country's unemployment situation came as a
result of the annual rebound in construction sector and other
outdoor jobs.
</P>
<P>
Exceptionally mild weather had also contributed to the
increased hiring, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
