<HEADLINE> Chilean President Meets Chinese Military Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei
today met a visiting Chinese military delegation headed by Zhang
Wannian, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission of China.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, they said they were satisfied with the
great development in the relationship between the two countries
and two armies.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said the visit is aimed to promote mutual understanding
and friendship between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
He also introduced the defensive military policy of China --
never seeking hegemony, non-interference in others' internal
affairs, non-military alignment and not sending troops to other
countries or building military bases aboard.
</P>
<P>
Frei said that he agreed to the Chinese defense policy and the
two countries, which have identical military policy, should push
forward their relationship.
</P>
<P>
He also said that exchange of visits by senior leaders between
the two countries is helpful to the development of the bilateral
relationship.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation arrived in Santiago on April 4 for a
four-day visit here following a four-day visit to Argentina. It
will go to Brazil later to complete its South American tour.
</P>
</TEXT>
