<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continue to rise on
the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index gained another 16.57 points to close at 2,104.71 points
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 142.3 million units,
valued at 347.96 million Singapore dollars (about 241.64 million
US dollars). Advances overwhelmed declines by 262 to 56, while 286
other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Ber Ind. was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 5.03 million units. It was followed by JSH 500 which
had 4.05 million shares traded. MBF Holdings was next with 3.8
million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
City Development Warrant 98 led the gainers of the day as it
rose by 60 cents to finish at 11.3 Singapore dollars. Samanda
Holdings gained 55 cents to end at 8.85 Singapore dollars, while
City Development, the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign,
and the Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign picked
up by 40 cents each to close at 14.1, 19, and 18.6 Singapore
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, GE Life was the biggest loser of the day as it
declined by 40 cents to end at 20 dollars. Malaya Cement fell by
25 cents to close at 2.81 dollars, while KL Kepong finished 16
cents lower at 3.64 dollars.  
</P>
