But in Kampala, Rebecca Kadaga, the State Minister for
Regional Cooperation, said the government will not negotiate with
LRA unless parliament reconsiders its last month's resolutions
rejecting direct peace talks between the government and the
rebels. Kadaga was reacting to Obita's proposal on peace raised
last Saturday on the London conference.
</P>
<P>
