<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Product Market to Remain Stable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China's manufactured goods market
will remain stable in 1997 with prices increasing at a similar
level as in 1996, according to the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said that it drew the conclusion after analysis of
the industrial product market in 1996.
</P>
<P>
It noted that 1996's industrial development provided a
favorable environment for the 1997's industrial product market.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the price index increased by 2.9 percent for
industrial products, 11.9 percentage points lower than in
1995. The figure was the lowest since 1985.
</P>
<P>
The market for the means of production maintained a balance in
1996, with price increasing by 3.5 percent over the previous year,
the lowest since 1990.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, with abundant supply of consumer goods, the price
for consumer products increased by only 2.1 percent, for the first
time since 1994 lower than that for the means of production.
</P>
<P>
The bureau attributed the stable market in 1996 to an
appropriate economic growth rate, twice dropping loan interest
rats by the central bank, and the abundant supply of industrial
products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970408.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: China Witnesses Rapid Growth of High-Tech Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- To maintain the rapid momentum of
its high-tech industry, China expects to shape seven high-tech
industrial development belts by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The seven belts will be formed around Suzhou-Wuxi-Changzhou in
east China's Jiangsu Province, Pearl River delta areas, Shandong
Peninsula, Liaodong Peninsula, areas along Beijing-Tianjin-Tanggu
expressway, Southeastern Fujian Province, and Shaanxi-Shanxi
provinces, an official with the State Science and Technology
Commission said.
</P>
<P>
He said the new development belts are expected to "turbocharge"
a great leap forward of Chinese economy in early next century.
</P>
<P>
Wang Ruiming, director of Torch Program of the State Science and
Technology Commission, said China's high-tech zones will promote
their cooperation with foreign countries in personnel training and
further strengthen technological cooperation with the US and
Russia.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that 15,000 new and high-tech enterprises
have been set up at China's 110 high-tech industrial development
zones, which employed 1.2 million people by the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Those businesses have realized 24 billion yuan (three billion
US dollars) of pre-tax profits and their export value reached 3.8
billion US dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Experts here believed that high and new technology of the 1990s
and the 21st century will be the major force for advancing the
world economy.
</P>
<P>
China began implementing in late 1988 its "torch program" aimed
at commercialization, industrialization, and internationalization
of high and new technological research findings.
</P>
<P>
The projects in high and new technology zones cover new
materials, biological technology, electronics and information,
integration of machinery and electronics, new energy, and
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Eight-year implementation of the "torch program" proved that
high-tech industry plays an ever more important role in China's
economy, science, technology, and social development.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that China launched more than 6,400 "torch
program" projects from 1991 to 1995 and realized 37.3 billion yuan
(4.6 billion dollars) of pre-tax profits.
</P>
<P>
In China's leading industrial city, Shanghai, the number of
high-tech ventures rose by 20 percent annually from 1994 to
1996. The total output value of the high-tech ventures had an
increase of 18 billion yuan (2.25 billion dollars) from 1994 to
1996.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech ventures also help technical retooling of
outdated state-own enterprises and bring along regional economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
Internationalization is one of the unique features of the
"torch program." So far, the Sino-foreign jointly-run China Torch
Foundation and China Foundation for Science and Technological
Development have absorbed some 200 million US dollars of foreign
funds.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Chinese high-tech zones have forged extensive,
cooperative ties and contacts with more than 20 countries and
regions. And these zones also introduce personnel, technology and
administration experience and information from other countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970408.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Defends Its Gas Deal With Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Energy and Natural
Resources Minister Recai Kutan has rebuffed a U.S. statement
criticizing Turkey's natural gas deal with Iran, saying it was a
wise choice to buy cheap Iranian energy.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters Monday during the Energy Forum '97
meeting held in Ankara, Kutan said that Turkey developed energy
cooperation with Iran because the most important and cheapest
source of natural gas for Turkey was Iran.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the U.S. had a double standard since it had
never reacted against the European countries which import oil from
Iran.
</P>
<P>
"If you compare natural gas with oil, you'll see that both of
them are hydrocarbons. The U.S. is reacting to the gas form of
hydrocarbons. It is impossible for the U.S. to justify its
attitude," Kutan added.
</P>
<P>
Since the Islamist Welfare Party led by Necmettin Erbakan came
to power last summer, energy-starved Turkey has enhanced its
economic cooperation with neighboring Iran, especially in the
energy field.
</P>
<P>
U.S. State Department spokesman Nicholas Burns criticized
Ankara in Washington last Friday for importing natural gas from
Iran.
</P>
<P>
The Energy Forum '97 meeting, which was organized by the
European Commission's energy agency, was called to discuss the
energy problems in the Black Sea region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970408.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
