<HEADLINE> 1 Palestinian Shot Dead by Israeli Settler </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A Palestinian youth was shot
dead by an Israeli settler in the West Bank city of Hebron this
morning, according to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian press
service based in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The settler opened fire randomly at Palestinians near the
Al-Ibrahimi Mosque in the city center, killing Issam Rashad
Kamel Arafeh, aged 17, and wounding four others.
</P>
<P>
This was the second incident in two days, involving Jewish
settler shooting Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, a settler of Dolev, north of Ramallah, shot and
wounded two Palestinians in the village of Harbata allegedly
after his car was hit by stones.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police arrested the man, whose name has not been
released, and confiscated his car and his M-16 automatic rifle.
</P>
<P>
The two incidents took place at a time when the
Israeli-Palestinian relations fell into an unprecedented deep
crisis since the Oslo Accords in 1993 as a result of the
right-wing Israeli government's aggressive policy of settlement
in the occupied Palestinian territories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
