<HEADLINE> Liu Huaqing Meets French Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Chairman of China's Central
Military Commission (CMC) Liu Huaqing met here today with Charles
Millon, the first French Defense Minister to visit China since the
two countries set up diplomatic relations in 1964.
</P>
<P>
Millon said that he hoped this visit will help step up
strategic dialogue and information exchanges between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
This kind of strategic dialogue should be carried out on a
regular basis, he said.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that Millon's visit is of great significance for
further development of the friendly cooperative relations between
the armed forces of the two countries. The two armed forces have
had sound relations in the past years, he said.
</P>
<P>
Since both countries play an important role in international
affairs, the development of a new friendly cooperative Sino-French
relationship that faces the 21st century will not only be in the
interests of the two peoples, but beneficial for the peace and
stability of the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
Liu, also a standing committee member of the Political Bureau
of the Chinese Communist Party's Central Committee, refuted the
theory of "China threat" that is disseminated by a handful of
people in the world, saying that China builds defense capability
for the sole purpose of self-defense.
</P>
<P>
Millon said that his visit to China will help maintain the
exchange of high-level visits by military leaders of the two
countries and strengthen the friendly cooperative relations
between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He said that France trusts China-- a nation that loves
peace. He said that France wishes to join efforts with China to
maintain peace and stability in the world.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the general staff of the
People's Liberation Army (PLA), and Cao Gangchuan, minister in
charge of the Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for
National Defense, attended the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
