He added that the economic cooperation between the two
countries helps strengthen and solidify the bilateral friendship
</P>
<P>
Noboru, who was in office from November 1987 to June 1989, said
that he would make efforts to develop the friendship and
cooperation between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Mitsuzuka said the Japanese government supports China's reform
and opening-up policy and backs China's bid for membership of the
World Trade Organization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
