<HEADLINE> IPU Conference to Open in Seoul on April 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The 97th Inter-Parliamentary
Conference will open here from April 10 to 15 to bring together
some 600 parliamentarians from around the world.
</P>
<P>
The six-day annual meeting of the International Parliamentary
Union (IPU) will be held at the invitation of the South Korean
parliament and opened by President Kim Young Sam.
</P>
<P>
It will be the second time that an IPU gathering has taken
place here since the nation joined the international group in
1964. The first meeting at this South Korean capital was in 1983.
</P>
<P>
Kim Soo-han, speaker of the host assembly, told a press
conference today that the forthcoming conference will focus on
cooperation for the world and regional security.
</P>
<P>
It will also discuss ways to respect for all forms of the
sovereignty and independence of states, and to change production
and consumption patterns for sustainable growth, he said.
</P>
<P>
Women parliamentarians will meet on the eve of the conference
to discuss in particular the theme "education as a means to
prevent the sexual exploitation of children."
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also study the steps taken at national level
to implement the IPU's 1994 Plan of Action, the Declaration and
Platform of the 4th World Conference on Women and the Beijing
Parliamentary Declaration.
</P>
<P>
A Chinese delegation led by Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, will be
here to attend the meeting. 
</P>
