<HEADLINE> Great Potential for China's Micro-electronics Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China will need a total of two
billion integrated circuits this year -- about 1.2 billion for
household appliances and 800 million for telecommunications
equipments, according to an official forecast.
</P>
<P>
Market demand for electronic components are also expected to
grow this year, to 150 billion units this year, said the forecast.
</P>
<P>
The market potential is attributed to China's determination to
focus its electronics industry on the telecommunications and
computers sector during the Ninth Five Year Plan (1996-2000)
period, explained a local official.
</P>
<P>
"China will give its top priority to the production of
integrated circuits, electronical components, computers, and
complete sets of electronic equipments," said the official.
</P>
<P>
The prospect is so attractive that international
micro-electronic producers are trying to get a foothold in the
market. some 500 company representatives from 22 countries and
regions, including the United States, Japan, Germany and
Switzerland, are coming to a Shanghai international exhibition on
electronic equipment and micro-electronics, scheduled to open on
May 6.  
