<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Registers 2.2 Percent Inflation in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Italy's consumer price index in March
rose 2.2 percent against the 2.4 percent level set for the
previous month, the National Statistics Bureau (ISTAT) said today.
</P>
<P>
The data show that the average inflation rate over the past 12
months was 3.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The greatest increases in consumer prices last month were
recorded in the sectors of housing, electricity and fuels, up 0.4
percent, which was caused by the increase in water rates and
heating fuels.
</P>
<P>
For transport and other goods and service, the prices climbed
by 0.3 percent over February as a result of hikes in automobiles
prices, gasoline, telephone and bank rates.
</P>
<P>
Consumer prices actually declined by 0.4 percent in the sectors
of recreation, entertainment and culture. For food, it was down
0.1 percent because of a decrease in bread and grains, meats,
fruits, fats and oils. 
</P>
</TEXT>
