<HEADLINE> World's Second Largest Panel For Beijing Aquarium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A million-dollar plate of glass
made in the United States has been transported to Beijing Zoo,
to be installed in the Beijing Aquarium as the second largest
aquarium panel in the world.
</P>
<P>
The 10-meter-long, six-meter-high, and 23-ton-weight glass wall
is second in size only next to the one installed in an aquarium in
San Francisco, in the US. The other 16-meter-long and
5.5-meter-high window designed for the sharks pool has also
arrived.
</P>
<P>
Made of acrylic, the windows are all better than ordinary
glasses as far as their transparency and solidity are
concerned. Although the glass is 22 centimeters wide, its
transparency reaches 99 percent.
</P>
<P>
"The Beijing Aquarium's need for acrylic panels constitutes
almost half of the total world market demand in 1995," said Zheng
Gong, manager of the business department of the Beijing Landa
Aquarium Co. Ltd, which undertakes the Beijing Aquarium project.
</P>
<P>
The aquarium, co-sponsored by Beijing Zoo and Pexlanda
International Ltd. of Hong Kong, will occupy an area of 35,000 sq
m in Beijing Zoo, with a total investment of 56 million US
dollars. The construction of the project is underway and the
aquarium is expected to go into operation in early next year.
</P>
</TEXT>
