<HEADLINE> Overseas-Funded Enterprises Thriving in Shandong Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Foreign-funded enterprises have
given a great impetus to economic development in east China's
Shandong Province, contributing more than half of local export
earnings last year, or nearly 5.5 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 10,405 overseas-financed enterprises,
earning more than 122 billion yuan in sales and 5.3 billion yuan
in profits last year.
</P>
<P>
The amount of overseas investment in Shandong last year
accounted for nearly 15 percent of the provincial total investment
in fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
And 20 percent of tax revenues of the province last year was
from the foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 11 percent of the number of Shandong's work force, or
1.15 million people, are now working for foreign-funded
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Improved investment environment has encouraged overseas
companies to increase investment in Shandong, in a bid to make big
profits in the coastal province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
