<HEADLINE> HKBA Joins in Ranks for HK's Handover Celebration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Basketball
Association (HKBA) has joined in the ranks to celebrate the
historic handover of Hong Kong at the midnight on June 30 this
year with a tournament under a new title.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's annual Super Commercial Cup has been renamed as
Henderson Cup this year as part of the celebrations. And the June
1-7 tournament will have the participation of China's national
team.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team for the international event will include
leading players from the professional league and is, according to
HKBA officials on Monday, stronger than China's Olympic side at
last year's Atlanta Games.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the Hong Kong Football Association (HKFA) announced
a star-studded match on July 3 this year between a FIFA all-star
team and their counterparts from Asia.
</P>
<P>
And the Hong Kong Tennis Association was reported by local
press to meet next week to discuss the possibility of organizing a
special event for the handover. 
</P>
</TEXT>
