<HEADLINE> Guangdong Cracks down on Fake Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 8 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
dealt with 32,533 cases of fake products last year, valued at 540
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province has made initial success in the campaign against
fake and shoddy products, according to the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
During the year, the province shut down 2,021 workshops for
producing fake goods and destroyed 248 million yuan-worth of such
goods.
</P>
<P>
The province, an economic powerhouse in China, became a key
spot for producing fake goods in recent years.
</P>
<P>
To protect consumers' interests, the provincial government
redoubled its efforts to crack down on the production and sales
of fake goods.
</P>
<P>
Leading government officials at various levels are asked to
take the job upon themselves and the people are being encouraged
to cooperate.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province launched a thorough check of 21 key
markets and severely punished the illegal stands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
