<HEADLINE> Hebei Improves Development Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Development zones in north
China's Hebei Province have spurred economic growth by expanding
an export-oriented economy, according to the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 19 economic and technological development
zones and two national-level hi-tech development zones, covering
the provincial coastal and inland areas.
</P>
<P>
In addition to preferential policies for overseas investors,
the province has attached great importance to the local investment
environment involving approval, establishment, and management of
overseas-funded projects.
</P>
<P>
The 21 development zones poured a total of 452 million
yuan into infrastructure last year. By the end of last year the
zones had developed a total of nearly 100 square kilometers of
land and improved facilities involving telecommunications, energy,
transportation, and water supply.
</P>
<P>
The zones brought in 280 million US dollars of overseas funds
last year, a 84 percent rise from the previous year, accounting
for 23 percent of the total of overseas funds in the province.
</P>
<P>
The development zones scored a total turnover of 10 billion
yuan, up 45 percent from the previous year and handled exports
worth 240 million US dollars, up 83 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
