<HEADLINE> Mercosur, EU to Tighten Business Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Five hundred companies from the
South American trade bloc Mercosur and the European Union will
meet here on December 4 and 5 to promote trade links.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 companies from the four Mercosur members
(Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay) and 200 companies from
the 15 countries in the EU will take part in the fair to promote
products, services or technologies in agriculture, chemical
products, plastics and components, mining, metallurgy and tools,
textiles and clothing manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
The organizers hope partnerships can be formed in different
ways: as joint ventures, through technological cooperation
agreements, through technology transfer and through subcontracting
and manufacturing licensees.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay's Chamber of Commerce and Devnet, a United Nations
agency responsible for the Technological and Commercial
Information Promotion System (TIPS), will run the first of the
partnership meetings on the American continent.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony marking the opening of a series of EU-Mercosur
partnership meetings, was held here today.
</P>
<P>
Among the economic and commercial authorities attending the
ceremony were Joel Fessaguet, chief of the EU delegation in
Uruguay and Diego Balestra, president of Uruguay's Chamber of
Commerce. 
</P>
