<HEADLINE> Canada to Help Rwandan Refugees in Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 7 (Xinhua ) -- The Canadian International
Development Agency (CIDA) will contribute three million
U.S. dollars to ensure the safe return of Rwandan refugees
currently in Zaire, said an official here today.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian International Cooperation Minister Don Boudria
said that he welcomed the decision of the alliance in Zaire to
allow the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) to
assist refugees in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The UNHCR has confirmed that Alliance Leader Laurent-Desire
Kabila has assured its officials that he will allow them to
transport Rwandan refugees from the Kisangani region of
northeastern Zaire back to Rwanda. The repatriation effort, in
which 100,000 people will be transported by land and air, is to
begin as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Canada has contributed a total of 11.4 million dollars in
fiscal year 1996-1997 to assist displaced persons and refugees who
were victims of the conflict in Zaire. 
</P>
