<HEADLINE> Japan to Enhance Investment, Cooperation in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 8 (Xinhua) - Japan's Chamber of Commerce and
Industry (CCI) has reached a memorandum of understanding with its
Myanmar counterpart to enhance its investment and cooperation in
the country.
</P>
<P>
The official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar said the MOU
was signed on Monday.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Myanmar Deputy Prime Minister and chairman of
the Foreign Investment Commission Maung Maung Khin met with the
CCI's leader Tadayoshi Nakazawa, who is also a vice-Chairman of
the Itochu Corporation, and they had discussions on promotion of
economic cooperation between the two countries and investment
matters, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Japan's investment in Myanmar amounted to over 192 million U.S.
dollars in 13 permitted projects out of the total foreign
investment of over six billion U.S. dollars from 21 countries and
regions by the end of February this year, according to the latest
official statistics.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
