<HEADLINE> China's Vice Premier Visits Finland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier Wu Bangguo
arrived here today for a three-day visit aiming to reinforce ties
with Finland.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued on his arrival, Wu said he has
come here to enhance the friendship and cooperation between China
and Finland.
</P>
<P>
Wu said China and Finland cherish a traditional friendship.
Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to Finland in 1995 and last
year's visit to China by Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari have
promoted the friendship to a new stage.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Wu will meet senior Finnish leaders and
businessmen and will visit factories and enterprises. Finland is
the fourth leg of Wu's 15-day European tour which has taken him to
Ukraine, Belarus and the Czech Republic and will also take him to
Sweden. 
</P>
</TEXT>
