<HEADLINE> Mauritius Foreign Minister to Visit Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Mauritius Foreign Minister Paul
Raymond Berenger will visit Sri Lanka from April 10-13, according
to a press release by the Foreign Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Berenger is scheduled to meet Prime
Minister Sirimavo Bandaranaike and other government ministers.
</P>
<P>
He will hold talks with his Sri Lankan counterpart Lakshman
Kadirgamar on bilateral relations and issues of common interest,
the release said.
</P>
<P>
Berenger is the current chairman of the Indian Ocean Rim
Association for Regional Cooperation (IORARC), of which the Sri
Lankan foreign minister is one of the two vice chairmen. The
other is the Omani minister of state for foreign affairs.
</P>
</TEXT>
