<HEADLINE> China, Czech Republic Have Great Potential for Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- There is great potential for China
and the Czech Republic to enhance trade ties between them, Chinese
Vice Premier Wu Bangguo said here today.
</P>
<P>
Wu, who arrived here on April 3 for a five-day visit, made the
remarks when he met Czech Industry and Trade Minister Vladimir
Dlouhy.
</P>
<P>
He said his trip aimed to strengthen the development of
the bilateral relations, particularly trade ties, between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to boost trade ties with the Czech Republic on
the basis of equality and mutual benefit, Wu said. He added the
two countries should take measures to promote mutual understanding
and increase the varieties of goods for export.
</P>
<P>
He said the two governments should encourage and support the
contact and cooperation between the industrial sectors, firms and
localities of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Dlouhy said the Czech government has been watching Chinese
economic development with great interest.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Czech economies can complement each other, and the
Czech Republic is willing to play a part in China's economic
development, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the Czech Republic supports China joining the World
Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
Wu ended his five-day official visit to the Czech Republic
earlier in the day, the third leg of his five-nation European
tour, which has taken him to Ukraine and Belarus. Wu will also
visit Finland and Sweden. 
</P>
</TEXT>
