<HEADLINE> Belgium Wants To Invest More in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Belgian Prime Minister Jean Luc
Dehaene said today in this capital that his country wants to
increase its future investments in Chile in the fields of energy,
copper, transportation and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Dehaene said that Belgium has opened its doors to the Chilean
market with investments in the energy and copper mines which are
of great interest to them.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister of Belgium arrived in Chile last Friday to
pay an official visit to this South American country. This
morning he was received by President Frei. On this ocasion both
leaders analyzed the bilateral relations between the European
Union and the Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
Within the framework of his visit, the two governments signed a
protocol of consultation between their foreign ministries today.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister will meet tomorrow with 40 Chilean
businessmen to evaluate the possibility of increasing bilateral
trade between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Last year, trade between Chile and Belgium reached 383 million
dollars, of which 64.5 percent corresponded to Chilean exports,
while 35.5 percent were imports from that European country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
