<HEADLINE> Myanmar Calls for Cooperation with KNU in Regional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar government always
invites the remaining Kayin National Union (KNU) to participate
cooperatively in regional development, Myanmar leader Khin Nyunt
was quoted by today's official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The KNU is the largest anti-government armed group in Myanmar
which has not yet made peace with the government.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar State Law and Order
Restoration Council, made the remarks at a meeting with Chairman
of the Burma Communist Party (Rakhine state) U Saw Tun Oo during
an inspection tour of the country's Rakhine state.
</P>
<P>
U Saw Tun Oo surrendered to the government with 289 members of
his party on Monday. The government described the event as an
exchange of arms for peace.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt said 16 armed groups in the country including the
Mong Tai Army (MTA), led by former drug warlord Khun Sa, have
already "exchanged arms for peace."
</P>
<P>
Khin Myunt called for harmonious cooperation in ensuring peace
in the whole country and building a modern and developed nation.
</P>
</TEXT>
