<HEADLINE> HK Investment Tianjin's Real Estate Sector Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Business people from Hong Kong
(HK) have started over 400 real estate development projects in
Tianjin, the largest port city of north China.
</P>
<P>
HK investment on these projects total 2.2 billion U.S. dollars,
according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong businessmen have altogether launched 10,000
investment projects in this northern Chinese city, involving a
total investment of 16 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Most of the HK investment has gone to industrial and trading
projects. Real estate sector ranks third in investment volume.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong leads other countries and regions in the number of
businesses started and the amount of investment on real estate
projects launched in this port city.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong New World Development Co. LTD, one of Hong Kong's
ten major consortia, has founded Tianjin New World Comfortable
Living Development Co. LTD. in cooperation with the Tianjin
Construction and Development Corporation. The new company will
construct apartment buildings with a total floor space of 1.2
million sq m.
</P>
<P>
Construction of a residential area for teachers and professors,
with a total floor space of 240,000 sq m, has just been completed
by the two partners.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have agreed to demolish the dilapidated buildings on
42 ha of Tianjin's downtown area and on 160 ha of the city's
outlying areas and construct apartment buildings on those places
in five years.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Lee Shau Kee, another prominent Hong Kong
businessman, came to Tianjin and signed a long-term cooperation
agreement with the Tianjin Municipal Government, expressing the
wish to invest in the city's real estate sector.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Municipal Government has also worked out a range of
preferential policies involving prices of land, and taxation, to
encourage overseas investors to develop the real estate sector,
said the sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
