<HEADLINE> ASEAN FMs to Meet to Decide Hopefuls' Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The foreign ministers of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) will meet
informally in Kuala Lumpur in May to decide whether Cambodia, Laos
and Myanmar will be admitted to the grouping this year.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the seven ASEAN members will put
forward their respective decisions and give reasons at a one-day
meeting on May 31, according to the Nation daily today, quoting
Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab Chaiyasarn.
</P>
<P>
Last July, ASEAN agreed to admit the three countries
simultaneously. But if one of the applicants is rejected, the
other two will not be able to join.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers' informal decision on the matter would be
submitted to their formal meeting scheduled for July in Malaysia
for a final and formal ruling.
</P>
<P>
Western countries have criticised ASEAN for wanting to reach
their goal of including all 10 Southeast Asian countries into the
forum by ignoring the situation in Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines,
Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.  
</P>
</TEXT>
