<HEADLINE> Russia, Lebanon Sign Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Lebanon today signed a
package of intergovernmental agreements on scientific, cultural
and educational cooperation, and the setting up of an
intergovernmental commission on trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The accords were signed soon after Lebanese Prime Minister
Rafik Hariri arrived in Moscow on a three-day official visit, the
first ever visit to Russia by a Lebanese premier since the two
countries established diplomatic relations in 1945.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also modified an agreement on trade and economic
cooperation signed in Beirut in 1995.
</P>
<P>
At a press briefing today, Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin said that during Hariri's visit, the two countries
are also likely to sign an agreement to avoid dual taxation, and
an agreement on mutual protection and encouragement of investment.
</P>
<P>
Russia "has fulfilled and will fulfill all agreements signed
with Lebanon," he said.
</P>
<P>
Describing his meeting with his Lebanese counterpart earlier
today as "good," he said Russia "is prepared to participate in the
rebuilding of Lebanon, in the construction of bridges and
implementation of utilities projects."
</P>
<P>
Moscow is also willing to provide Lebanon with a list of
projects in Russia in which Lebanese enterprises could
participate, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
