<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Beats Azerbaijan 3-0 in 4-nation Field Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Favourite China recorded its
second win at the four-nation Golden Jubilee Women International
field Hockey Tournament on Monday after beating Azerbaijan 3-0.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan suffered their second successive defeat in the
five-day event being held in Lahore, capital of Pakistan's Punjab
province when they were beaten by Singapore 3-1 on the second day,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
China which crushed Pakistan 10-0, established 3-0 supremacy
against Azerbaijan after wasting five penalty corner due to
erratic shooting and lack of planning.
</P>
<P>
Out of their seventeen short corners, China earned twelve in
the second half but surprisingly failed to exhibit required
technique to score in direct or indirect drills.
</P>
<P>
Azerbaijan custodian Nokuline did excellent job under the bar
by foiling most off these sitters with brave clearance from mid of
the circle.
</P>
<P>
Azerbiajan defence proved a house of cards when Liu Lijie, Cai
Xuemei, Li Congrong, Qu Bo anticipated skilful stick work plus
vast stamina to create scoring opportunities.
</P>
<P>
China settled down in the 5th minute when Gao Min found roof
nets and five minutes later Lu Feng enhanced lead in a field
attack. Gao scored her second goal after beating entire defence
and goalkeeper with a lively sprint pushing the ball in the left
corner in the 21st minute.
</P>
<P>
China took full control in the second half and gained six
penalty corners in seven minutes but failed to score.
</P>
<P>
After another three penalty corners right winger Li Congrong
added the third goal, three minutes before final whistle in a goal
mouth scramble.
</P>
<P>
Tomorrow is the rest day and China will play Singapore
on April 9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
