BONN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Former world number one Steffi Graf
of Germany had not fully recovered from the left knee injury,
Graf's manager Hans Engert said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
27-year-old Graf is not certain of returning for the Hamburg
tennis tournament which starts on April 28.
</P>
<P>
Engert said that Graf's injury has been bothering her for
several months.
</P>
<P>
The manager added that Graf still felt pain despite intensive
treatment from the Austrian physio who treated former men's
skiing great Franz Klammer and could not resume full training.
</P>
<P>
It had hoped that Hamburg would be the venue for a first
opportunity for Graf to duel it out with 16-year-old Martina
Hingis of Switzerland, who became the youngest-ever world number
one player when she assumed Graf's spot last Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
