<HEADLINE> Beef Production In Brazil Dropping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's beef production
will drop 4 percent to 6.05 million tons this year compared with
that in 1996, said the National Federation of Meat Production.
</P>
<P>
The main reason for the lower output is the 1.3 percent
reduction in the number of heads of cattle, i.e. 1.44 million,
according to today's press reports.
</P>
<P>
The per capita consumption of beef will contract 5.5 percent
this year to 37.3 kilograms a year per inhabitant.
</P>
<P>
Imports of beef will increase 11.9 percent this year compared
with last year, i.e. from 143,000 to 160,000 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
