<HEADLINE> UNICEF Names Weah Its Envoy for Sport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Children's Fund
UNICEF named Liberia's soccer star George Weah its ambassador for
sport on Monday and said he would play a special role in raising
awareness about AIDS and child victims of war.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Milan, The AC Milan club striker was
appointed to the position at a ceremony in Milan.
</P>
<P>
UNICEF regional director Andre Roberfroid said in a
statement: "Having lived with the hostilities in his native
Liberia, Weah commands the understanding necessary to devote
special attention to the particular needs of children in the midst
of conflict."
</P>
<P>
The Statement said Weah would also work closely with the UNAIDS
agency to "mobilise the global football community to play a larger
role in HIV/AIDS prevention and care".
</P>
<P>
UNICEF has a host of celebrity "special representatives" who
donate their services in support of the agency's work. 
</P>
