<DOCNO> XIE19970408.0291 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Shares up on Wall Street's Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Major European stock markets
extended last Friday's recovery and all ended sharply higher
Monday, supported by a firmer Wall Street and the strength of the
dollar.
</P>
<P>
The London market, the largest in Europe, closed just off its
session high, 35.1 points up at 4,271.7, helped by a sharp rise on
Wall Street in early trading.
</P>
<P>
But dealers said that lingering worries about higher interest
rates and political uncertainties ahead of Britain's general
election tempered London's advance.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, share prices ended with good gains, driven by
Wall Streent's recovery last Friday and higher bonds, against
expectations, with the DAX-30 index 67.95 points higher at
3,312.88.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that chemicals and banks benefited from the
dollar's strength.
</P>
<P>
Shares on the Paris bourse also closed sharply higher on the
back of the Dow's rally, a strong domestic bonds market and the
dollar's revival, with the CAC-40 index 54.34 points up at
2,572.31.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index of leading British shares ended up 35.1
points at 4,271.7. The Frankfurt DAX-30 index finished 67.95
points higher at 3,312.88. In Paris, the CAC-40 index closed 54.34
points firmer at 2,572.31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
