<HEADLINE> Dow Continues to Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
moved higher modestly again on Monday, propelled largely by major
technology shares.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones finally rose 29.84 points to 6,555.91.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock measures also advanced for the second session as
bond-market interest rates backed away from Friday's seven-month
high.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by more than a 2-to-1
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume was relatively
light at 453.42 million shares, down from 537.27 million on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The S&AMP;P 500 rose 4.23 to 762.13, and the NYSE composite index
rose 2.66 to 400.68. The Nasdaq composite index rose 14.62 to
1,251.35, and the American Stock Exchange composite index rose
3.71 to 560.44.
</P>
<P>
But many investors still held that a correction is not over and
major stock indexes might move down again.
</P>
<P>
Stocks also gained support in the bond market, where prices
rebounded, lowering the yield on the 30-year Treasury bond to 7.06
percent. On Friday, the yield shot to 7.12 percent, the highest
closing level since September.
</P>
<P>
IBM, which slid sharply last week amid fears the computer giant
won't meet earnings expectations, was the Dow's strongest issue
Monday. In Nasdaq trading, meanwhile, Cisco Systems and Microsoft
also rose remarkably.
</P>
<P>
The Dow's other big gainer was Boeing which rose after The Wall
Street Journal reported that the leading aircraft maker is
preparing to increase its production pace by 10 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
