<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Disaster Declared for Dakotas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The federal government Monday
declared a state of "major disaster" in the states of North Dakota
and South Dakota as a result of heavy storms and flooding over the
past weeks.
</P>
<P>
The declarations make affected residents and business owners
eligible for federal grants and loans to help them repair damaged
and lost property, and prevent such damages in the future.
</P>
<P>
The White House made the announcement after Senate Democratic
leader Tom Daschle and other members of the congressional
delegations from the two states met Monday with President Bill
Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Daschle and his colleagues said Clinton agreed almost
immediately to provide the declarations, as well as to dispatch a
federal team to the area led by James Lee Witt, director of the
Federal Emergency Management Agency.
</P>
<P>
Witt said he expected a request for a disaster declaration
Tuesday from the governor of Minnesota, which is fighting floods
and winter storms that have left snow removal equipment frozen in
solid ice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
