<HEADLINE> Greece: One in Five Greek Companies in Albania Destroyed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- One in five Greek enterprises in
Albania have been destroyed in the recent riot, a report released
by the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) from Tirana said
today.
</P>
<P>
An inventory being carried out by the Greek Embassy's
commercial section has so far reported damages at 60 of the 250
Greek-owned businesses in the strife-ridden Albania.
</P>
<P>
The damage to each of these was reportedly valued at between
200-400 million drachmas (about 52,000 to 1,04 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The collapse of pyramid investment schemes sparked nationwide
protests in Albania which later spilled over into armed conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Most enterprised, including Greek-owned ones, remain closed due
to continuing fears of attacks by robbers.
</P>
<P>
During a recent visit to Athens by Albanian Prime Minister
Bashkim Fino, a group of Greek businessmen had presented him with
a petition calling for protection by Tirana of their investments.
they also requested compensation for the damages they suffered.
</P>
<P>
Fino had pledged to take measures to protect Greek businessmen
in his country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
