<HEADLINE> China, Other East Asian Countries Presented at Los </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles, April 7 (Xinhua) --Ancient civilization and
oriental features of east Asian countries were highlighted ar a
travel show here ending last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Travel agencies from China, Thailand, India, Indonesia,
Malaysia and Singapore presented attractive programs at the 22nd
Los Angeles Times Travel Show to lure American tourists.
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles is one of the nation's most lucrative travel
markets. More than 200 wholesale tour operators, airlines,
resorts, participated in the show, which was visited by 21,000
people.
</P>
<P>
The replica of two famous life-size terra cotta warriors, the
greatest archeological discoveries in this century, stood
permanently at the booth representing Los Angeles-based China
National Tourist Office.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 million Americans go abroad every year as
tourists, visiting places from neighboring Mexico and Canada, to
Europe, the Caribbean countries and the Far East.
</P>
<P>
China, Japan, Singapore and South Korea are the leading
destinations for Americans traveling in east Asia. Hong Kong is
always a stop wherever they go.
</P>
<P>
According to a manager of the China National Tourist Office, a
total of 6.74 million foreign tourists, including 570,000
Americans, visited China last year. Admissions of visitors from
Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan totaled more than 40 million.
</P>
<P>
The office is promoting "Discover China 97", and "Rediscover
China" programs in the United States for both new and old
visitors. Thousands of copies of booklets on the programs were
asked for at the show. 
</P>
</TEXT>
