<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Launches Pilot Projects to Boost Local Employment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission has
launched eight pilot projects on the information society and its
link to employment and local development, it was learned here
today.
</P>
<P>
Each project will develop local strategies and action plans and
will be based on wide regional consensus on how to integrate the
information society concept into employment and development
policies at the local level.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the initiative, Padraig Flynn, European
commissioner responsible for employment and social affairs, said,
"Strong local involvement is the key to ensuring that the impact
of ICTs (information and communication technologies) on skill
requirements and employment policy is seized upon as an
opportunity and not a risk."
</P>
<P>
The projects will run for between 18 and 24 months, each
receiving up to 250,000 ECUs (some 325,000 U.S. dollars) of
co-financing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
